HEADWORD: Snowberry
<hw>Snow"ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A name of several shrubs with white berries; as, the
<spn>Symphoricarpus racemosus</spn> of the Northern United States, and
the <spn>Chiococca racemosa</spn> of Florida and tropical
America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Creeping snowberry</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Creeping</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snowbird</ent>⟦br⟧
